Turkish Police Detain Member of Hezbollah’s Armed Wing in Raid

-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 
2011-10-22T08:33:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/turkish-police-detain-member-of-hezbollah-s-armed-wing-in-raid.html
Turkish police detained a commander
of Hezbollah’s armed wing after a raid in Sanliurfa near the
Syrian border, the state-run Anatolia news agency reported.  The man, identified as Cemil M., was recently sentenced to
life in prison by a Turkish court and had been on the run from
the authorities, Anatolia said, citing the police. Hezbollah is
backed by Iran and  Syria  and is classified as a terrorist group
by the U.S. and  Israel .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  